Objective :

DONE - 1. $ java TheCube -mode=fildefer | -mode=facesvisibles
DONE - 2. 1 cube = 8 lignes de 3 floattant sur fichier d'entrée
DONE - 3. à l'aide des boutons tourner dans l'espace(centre cube immobile)
DONE - 4. afficher après chaque usage de bouton
DONE - 4'. Perspective ?

Usage :

Launch it via command-line :
    java org.blackpanther.Launcher [--fill] [-1 -1 -1 ...]

Every parameter are optional :

    draw mode : [default: line]
        by passing '--fill' to the program,
        you choose to display only visible face of the cube

    cube : [default: a cube with BCGF only visible face]
        by passing exactly 8 3-dimensional point data,
        separated by space, you can override this default cube to your own.